---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Case studies — Gian Trotta"
  description="Real before-and-after website rescues: measurable speed, search visibility, and cost results for small businesses."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Case studies</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-mist">
      Before-and-after, with real numbers.
    </p>

    <a
      href="/case-studies/rusty/"
      class="mt-12 block border border-line bg-white p-8 transition-colors hover:border-ink"
    >
      <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare-deep">Website Rescue</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 font-display text-2xl font-bold">
        Rusty the Raccoon — a children's book site, off Wix
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-mist">
        A children's book author was paying $400 a year for a Wix site that told Google its name
        was "My Site." Now it costs nothing to host, loads in under 2 seconds instead of over 6,
        and Google actually knows what it is.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 font-semibold text-steel">Read the case study →</p>
    </a>

    <a
      href="/case-studies/fresh-beginnings/"
      class="mt-6 block border border-line bg-white p-8 transition-colors hover:border-ink"
    >
      <p class="font-utility text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-flare-deep">Site refresh</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 font-display text-2xl font-bold">
        Fresh Beginnings Publishing — already fast, made findable
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-mist">
        A publisher's site loaded fast, but search engines and AI assistants barely knew it
        existed. Now it shows up in Google, is verified with Google Search Console, and got a
        visual refresh too.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 font-semibold text-steel">Read the case study →</p>
    </a>
  </section>
</Base>
